[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test fixture structure**\n\nI'm thinking about whether to create a separate public test fixture file, keeping in mind the requirement for a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files. It seems like adding an extra fixture file might go against this rule. Each dynamic-access class should be covered in a dedicated Java test file, but I wonder if including a package-private top-level fixture in the same file would work. However, all top-level test classes must be public, so I’m debating if a fixture could be considered a test or not.\n\n**Evaluating static classes in tests**\n\nI'm considering how to restructure the TestClassScannerTest. It looks like the nested static class might be difficult to extend. I think I could skip the superclass and focus on just getting the declared classes at the call site. The source comments mention the superclass, but perhaps it isn't necessary to cover both. I believe I can simplify the test assertion and increase behavior by using the top-level base. I’ll need to edit the file to implement these changes.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0dae95c566a243cc016a28e70708588196a8e1a6bca11b559c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKOckw6zkm89h4xlJa4Qjx4cMJG9GouW1mzo06bNjhdzn_ZWFxPF5ZRerIGwFuPh8-PXrYtUSDbvYiGCRTwEgo4z7ly500Upoc2BPiAEznMu-sM06JaFpMQzCzs929XmqSMIYAqQAh_poAPV-aJU8YGHi2JxF0cFQ3xZutLY6NZ20Ww0bMkIJemzD4voSayaWX-KuqChlLVKlIKLhpTyqaHswmAccA_WstWpULRcDXjMIIbD9rSuxyvUYnLYrxOOM3AVBYT8vONspRnjJ8Z3qVLhu5-AT0nHw30diM3N9fvgio4wjrkVI79rXFFaapmCELX04DpMajeW1bDRCoZcGLeNg043zeQf2hbk7f0rvTdIpSNplBbY_0VXKRyPSJja2ZSAy-WbEZygihDdNg6jBb_3QbUui5SY2Wafx0KtLZPeQaR_FW2mSVuZIOvNG2MoRob7lJhYEb_kGeUz-rw5f2OaCxBbbKnYFc8R48K_qZ_6w6Lr_RdhdnMrFijLJ3N2LEXblD5O8XvcFkBKKcnNxzFt6eHYMem2C3ArNUuhKfEcX8ZQQSkDzZ2I0l4fIuNRGDIru_qRDyPFBxodUNWZu7SEwi2VN96rHWJbqgwuHgFz